# Flagify Feature Flags

Project uses Flagify for feature management.
SDK: @flagify/node (server), @flagify/react (client)

## Patterns

Node.js:
```typescript
const flagify = new Flagify({ projectKey: '...', publicKey: 'pk_dev_...' })
await flagify.ready()
flagify.isEnabled('flag-name')                    // boolean
flagify.getValue('flag-name', fallback)           // typed value, fallback required
flagify.getVariant('flag-name', 'control')        // A/B variant
flagify.destroy()                                 // clean up SSE
```

React:
```typescript
// Wrap with <FlagifyProvider projectKey="..." publicKey="pk_dev_...">
const enabled = useFlag('flag-name')
const value = useFlagValue<T>('flag-name', fallback) // fallback required
const variant = useVariant('flag-name', 'control')
const ready = useIsReady()
```

## User context & targeting

For flags that differ per user (admins, plans, beta cohorts, geos): pass the user ONCE when the client/Provider initializes. The SDK fetches values already evaluated for that user, and `useFlag()` / `isEnabled()` return them from cache.

React — mount Provider below auth, with `key={user.id}` so the cache resyncs on login/logout:
```tsx
<FlagifyProvider
  key={user?.id ?? 'anonymous'}
  options={{"{{"}}
    realtime: true,
    user: user ? { id: user.id, role: user.role, email: user.email } : undefined,
  {{"}}"}}
>
  <App />
</FlagifyProvider>
const canSeeAdmin = useFlag('admin-tools') // already targeted
```

DO NOT write a custom React hook that calls `client.evaluate(key, user)` per flag.

Node per-request (Express/Fastify/Next):
```typescript
const result = await flagify.evaluate('admin-tools', { id: req.user.id, role: req.user.role })
if (!result.value) return res.status(403).end()
```

User object shape: `{ id, role?, email?, group?, plan?, ...customAttributes }`. Field is `id`, not `userId`. Targeting rules are configured server-side (dashboard/API), not in code.

## CLI

The CLI auto-detects non-TTY environments and skips confirmation prompts automatically.

- Flags: flagify flags list [--format json] | flagify flags get <key> [--format json] | flagify flags create <key> --type boolean|string|number|json | flagify flags toggle <key> --environment <env>
- Keys: flagify keys list --environment <env> | flagify keys generate --environment <env> | flagify keys revoke --environment <env>
- Typed keys: flagify types --typescript (./flagify.ts with FLAG_KEYS + FlagKey) | flagify types --go --package <pkg> (./flagify.go with FlagXxx consts). Regenerate on flag changes; prefer FLAG_KEYS['name'] over raw strings.
- Config: flagify config | flagify config set <key> <value>
- Valid config keys: api-url, workspace, project, environment
- Webhooks (env-scoped): flagify webhooks list [-e <env>] | flagify webhooks create -e <env> --name "..." --url https://... --events flag.created,flag.toggled | flagify webhooks deliveries <wh-id> | flagify webhooks delete <wh-id> --yes

## Webhooks

Outbound HTTP events. Each hook binds to ONE environment. Project-wide events (flag.created/updated/deleted/archived) fan out to every hook in the project; env-specific events (flag.toggled, targeting_rule.*) only reach hooks bound to that env. Signing secret shown exactly once at create — save it on the receiver as FLAGIFY_WEBHOOK_SECRET.

Verify the signature in Node.js with the raw body (Express: express.raw({ type: 'application/json' })). Signed input = `<X-Flagify-Timestamp>.<rawBody>`, HMAC-SHA256 keyed on the secret.

```typescript
import crypto from 'crypto'
function verifyFlagifySignature(req, body: Buffer, secret: string, toleranceSec = 300) {
  const m = (req.headers['x-flagify-signature'] || '').match(/t=(\d+),v1=([0-9a-f]+)/)
  if (!m) return false
  const [, ts, sig] = m
  if (Math.abs(Date.now() / 1000 - Number(ts)) > toleranceSec) return false
  const expected = crypto.createHmac('sha256', secret).update(`${ts}.${body.toString()}`).digest('hex')
  return crypto.timingSafeEqual(Buffer.from(sig, 'hex'), Buffer.from(expected, 'hex'))
}
```

Payload: { id, event, createdAt, data: { resource, actor, workspaceId, projectId, environmentId, metadata } }. data.environmentId always populated. metadata keys are snake_case (flag_key, environment_key, field, old_value, new_value, rule_count, ...) and vary per event. Use event.id as idempotency key — deliveries are at-least-once.

## Key types
- pk_* (publishable) — safe for client/browser
- sk_* (secret) — server-side only, never expose

## Conventions
- Flag names: kebab-case only — new-feature (no camelCase, snake_case, spaces)
- Group related flags: checkout-*, onboarding-*
- Always handle both flag states
- Fallback values required for getValue() / useFlagValue()
- For targeted flags: pass options.user to Provider/client ONCE — never call client.evaluate() from a React hook per flag

